Foods pretty bad, I gave it 2 stars because of the Queso Fundido.  I started off with a spicy margarita which was sweeter than it was spicy, they added way too much simple syrup. My drink hit the table, at no point in time did I ever get WATER, which is a basic necessity of any restaurant especially when you’re going to have to wash off that sugar from the margarita to taste the food. The queso fundido with chorizo was nice. I’m lucky I saved some of it for the enchiladas because they were by far the worst enchiladas I’ve ever had.  These were the bandera enchiladas and they were horrible, none of the 3 sauces had any flavor and the shrimp was still cold even though it took forever to get there. I ordered a Michelada, it was a pretty standard modelo Michelada nothing special about it except the price, the price was 12 dollars for a 6 dollar beer with lime juice, Valentina sauce, tobasco and a tajin rim. I asked for my Bill, and I put my card down, they swiped it without telling me there was a 20% auto-gratuity added to it, they should let you tip according to your experience, having an auto-gratuity creates a lazy service because you already know you’re getting tipped well no matter what. Overall I wouldn’t recommend it, I’d just walk down a block to “LOS 3 POTRILLOS” who have better tasting food/service at a fraction of the cost.
